BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then return "pause"	end tellend ifif application "iTunes" is running then	tell application "iTunes"		if player state is playing then return "pause"	end tellend ifif application "VLC" is running then	tell application "VLC"		if it is playing then return "pause"	end tellend ifreturn "play"

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: # This script requires two libs. Download them:# https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/json-helper-for-applescript/id453114608?l=en&mt=12 # https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/location-helper-for-applescript/id488536386?mt=12 tell application "Location Helper"	set clocation_coords to get location coordinates	log (item 1 of clocation_coords)	tell application "JSON Helper"		set lat to item 1 of clocation_coords		set lon to item 2 of clocation_coords		set date_day to day of (current date)		set date_month to month of (current date) as integer		set date_year to year of (current date)				# see https://aladhan.com/prayer-times-api		set api to "http://api.aladhan.com/v1/calendar?method=11&latitude=" & lat & "&longitude=" & lon & "&month=" & date_month & "&year=" & date_year				# shange comma to dot. Somehow the dot in lat and lon got changed to comma		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to the ","		set the item_list to every text item of api		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to the "."		set api to the item_list as string		set AppleScript's text item delimiters to ""				# adjust athan response		set api to api & "&methodSettings=20.0,null,18.0&tune=0,2,0,3,2,6,6,2"				set prayers to fetch JSON from api		set prayer to timings of item date_day of |data| of prayers		set fajr to item 1 of (my theSplit(fajr of prayer, " "))		set dhuhr to item 1 of (my theSplit(dhuhr of prayer, " "))		set asr to item 1 of (my theSplit(asr of prayer, " "))		set maghrib to item 1 of (my theSplit(maghrib of prayer, " "))		set isha to item 1 of (my theSplit(isha of prayer, " "))				set now to time string of (current date)		set now_hour to item 1 of (my theSplit(now, "."))		set now_minute to item 2 of (my theSplit(now, "."))		set now_total to (now_hour * 60) + now_minute		log (now_total)				set prayer_hour to item 1 of (my theSplit(fajr, ":"))		set prayer_minute to item 2 of (my theSplit(fajr, ":"))		set fajr_total to (prayer_hour * 60) + prayer_minute				set prayer_hour to item 1 of (my theSplit(dhuhr, ":"))		set prayer_minute to item 2 of (my theSplit(dhuhr, ":"))		set dhuhr_total to (prayer_hour * 60) + prayer_minute				set prayer_hour to item 1 of (my theSplit(asr, ":"))		set prayer_minute to item 2 of (my theSplit(asr, ":"))		set asr_total to (prayer_hour * 60) + prayer_minute				set prayer_hour to item 1 of (my theSplit(maghrib, ":"))		set prayer_minute to item 2 of (my theSplit(maghrib, ":"))		set maghrib_total to (prayer_hour * 60) + prayer_minute				set prayer_hour to item 1 of (my theSplit(isha, ":"))		set prayer_minute to item 2 of (my theSplit(isha, ":"))		set isha_total to (prayer_hour * 60) + prayer_minute				set prayer to "Fajr"		set prayer_time to fajr				if (now_total < isha_total) then			set prayer to "Isha"			set prayer_time to isha		end if				if (now_total < maghrib_total) then			set prayer to "Maghrib"			set prayer_time to maghrib		end if				if (now_total < asr_total) then			set prayer to "Asr"			set prayer_time to asr		end if				if (now_total < dhuhr_total) then			set prayer to "Dhuhr"			set prayer_time to dhuhr		end if				set prayer_hour to item 1 of (my theSplit(prayer_time, ":"))		set prayer_minute to item 2 of (my theSplit(prayer_time, ":"))		set prayer_total to (prayer_hour * 60) + prayer_minute				set next_prayer_diff to prayer_total - now_total		if (next_prayer_diff > 0 and next_prayer_diff ≤ 5) then			return prayer & " -00:0" & next_prayer_diff		end if				return prayer & " " & prayer_time			end tellend tellon theSplit(theString, theDelimiter)	-- save delimiters to restore old settings	set oldDelimiters to AppleScript's text item delimiters	-- set delimiters to delimiter to be used	set AppleScript's text item delimiters to theDelimiter	-- create the array	set theArray to every text item of theString	-- restore the old setting	set AppleScript's text item delimiters to oldDelimiters	-- return the result	return theArrayend theSplit

BTTTriggers.BTTPredefinedActionName: Run Apple Script (enter directly as text)
BTTTriggers.BTTInlineAppleScript: if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then			next track		end if	end tellend if

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: if application "Spotify" is running then	tell application "Spotify"		if player state is playing then			return (get artist of current track) & " – " & (get name of current track)		else			return ""		end if	end tellend ifreturn ""

BTTTriggerConfig.BTTTouchBarAppleScriptString: # This script requires two libs. Download them:# https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/json-helper-for-applescript/id453114608?l=en&mt=12 # https://itunes.apple.com/ru/app/location-helper-for-applescript/id488536386?mt=12 tell application "Location Helper"	set clocation_coords to get location coordinates	tell application "JSON Helper"		set weather to fetch JSON from "http://api.openweathermap.org/data/2.5/weather?lat=" & item 1 of clocation_coords & "&lon=" & item 2 of clocation_coords & "&units=metric&appid=32c4256d09a4c52b38aecddba7a078f6"		set temp to temp of main of weather as string		set cond_icon to icon of item 1 of weather of weather as string		if cond_icon is in ["01d", "01n"] then			set cond to "☀️"		else if cond_icon is in ["02d", "02n"] then			set cond to "⛅️"		else if cond_icon is in ["03d", "03n", "04d", "04n"] then			set cond to "☁️"		else if cond_icon is in ["09d", "09n"] then			set cond to "🌧"		else if cond_icon is in ["10d", "10n"] then			set cond to "🌦"		else if cond_icon is in ["11d", "11n"] then			set cond to "🌩"		else if cond_icon is in ["13d", "13n"] then			set cond to "❄️"		else if cond_icon is in ["50d", "50n"] then			set cond to "🌫"		else			set cond to ""		end if		set temp_round to round (temp * 1.0)		return cond & " " & temp_round & "°C"	end tellend tell
